03:15.458 --> 03:17.541
Mr. Sun is ten days late?

03:17.666 --> 03:20.000
He's forgotten all about us.

03:20.125 --> 03:21.500
Sorry the mail is late.

03:21.625 --> 03:24.583
Got so much ice on my wings,
I hadn't been cleared for take-off.

03:24.666 --> 03:26.458
Here, postcard from Mr. Sun.

03:28.958 --> 03:31.708
"Having a wonderful holiday.

03:31.833 --> 03:36.000
Perfect weather, as usual,
seems to follow me around.

03:36.083 --> 03:37.208
Oh!

03:37.500 --> 03:40.166
So, I'm going to stay a bit longer.

03:40.291 --> 03:42.541
Hope you don't mind. Smiley face."

03:42.666 --> 03:46.666
Uh, precisely how long is a bit?

03:46.791 --> 03:50.250
It better not be much or we'll freeze.

03:50.375 --> 03:53.708
I's already did.

03:54.458 --> 03:58.791
Hear that? That's what we'll be soon.
Frozen solid!

03:58.916 --> 04:03.000
We have think of a way to...
To stay warm.

04:03.125 --> 04:07.291
Let's do it... indoors.

04:10.791 --> 04:12.750
Uh-oh. Look.

04:16.958 --> 04:18.833
Why is that "uh-oh"?

04:18.958 --> 04:22.750
It's "uh-oh" because the
sunflower's come up too early,

04:22.875 --> 04:25.500
and that sunflower makes power
for our whole village.

04:25.625 --> 04:27.375
Absolutely correct, Kumi.

04:27.500 --> 04:30.583
When Mr. Sun comes out in the summer,

04:30.708 --> 04:33.375
the sunshine makes
the sunflower petals spin,

04:33.500 --> 04:36.541
which generates lots of elec-crick-ity.

04:36.666 --> 04:39.458
And the elec-crick-ity is stored

04:39.583 --> 04:43.791
in a special battery
for us to use all year round.

04:43.916 --> 04:46.541
Oh, I get it.

04:47.458 --> 04:48.833
What's "elec-crick-ity"?

04:48.958 --> 04:51.208
Elec-crick-ity
is what powers everything.

04:51.333 --> 04:53.791
If it wasn't for that
sunflower spinning around,

04:53.916 --> 04:55.750
we wouldn't have any power in winter

04:55.875 --> 04:58.375
for heaters or lights in our houses.

05:01.333 --> 05:04.583
-Yeah. You mean like now.
-And once the battery gives out...

05:06.208 --> 05:07.500
Like now.

05:07.625 --> 05:10.000
It'll get really, really brr.

05:10.125 --> 05:11.625
Like now.

05:11.750 --> 05:16.333
Yes. The sunflower must've
expected Mr. Sun last week.

05:16.458 --> 05:19.958
That's why it flowered too soon.

05:20.416 --> 05:24.458
And... And if anything
happens to that sunflower,

05:24.583 --> 05:29.208
we won't be able to make
anymore elec-crick-ity ever again.

05:29.333 --> 05:31.625
You're saying
we're definitely going to freeze.

05:31.750 --> 05:34.291
So-- So, how much time
do you think we have left?

05:34.416 --> 05:37.458
Crick? Kumi? How much time?!

05:37.583 --> 05:41.625
I'd tell you, Walter,
but my watch is frozen.

05:58.125 --> 06:01.541
Okay. Here's my plan:

06:01.666 --> 06:06.125
If we align the crickto-magnifier
just so...

06:06.208 --> 06:07.291
Whee!

06:07.625 --> 06:11.291
...it will focus all the heat
left in the sky,

06:11.416 --> 06:15.916
so, the sunflower
will feel warm as toast.

06:18.458 --> 06:22.625
As it appears, the sky
doesn't have any heat left.

06:23.083 --> 06:24.750
My apologies.

06:25.125 --> 06:26.875
It was a good plan, Crick.

06:27.833 --> 06:29.750
I don't want to alarm anyone,

06:29.875 --> 06:34.500
but my squish-sicle
is becoming a squish-berg!

06:36.208 --> 06:40.041
I will. I... I will think of something.

06:40.166 --> 06:41.875
I have to.

06:42.000 --> 06:44.625
Oh, think. Think!

06:48.666 --> 06:53.250
Uh... My, uh... brain is frozen.

06:54.458 --> 06:56.708
Guys! Guys! He's here!

06:56.833 --> 06:59.416
Mr. Sun is back!

07:05.000 --> 07:07.333
It's Mr. Sun! He's in there!

07:12.708 --> 07:17.541
Oh, it's not Mr. Sun. Sorry.

07:17.666 --> 07:19.791
Aw, it's okay, Buzz.

07:19.916 --> 07:22.958
Hey, if that little light...

07:23.083 --> 07:26.708
If it could fool us,
maybe it can fool the sunflower.

07:26.791 --> 07:30.291
-What do you say, Crick?
-It's worth a try.

07:37.041 --> 07:39.500
Here's my new plan:

07:39.625 --> 07:41.791
We lift the light up into the sky,

07:41.916 --> 07:46.666
and shine it through
my crickto-magnifier, then...

07:48.458 --> 07:50.958
No way. That may have
been our last chance.

07:51.083 --> 07:55.083
-The last-est?
-Our last-est chance?

07:55.208 --> 07:58.333
Stay calm, everyone. Stay calm!

07:58.458 --> 08:00.708
You know, I almost panicked
for a minute there,

08:00.833 --> 08:04.583
but now, I'm... totally in control!

08:04.708 --> 08:08.416
Bugs, we have to get a message
to Mr. Sun asking him to come back.

08:08.541 --> 08:12.083
Otherwise our sunflower
is gonna die, and then--

08:12.208 --> 08:14.125
Of course!

08:14.250 --> 08:17.458
We, uh... We could send a message
to Mr. Sun

08:17.583 --> 08:20.000
